7 charge privately paying parents.
8 (2) Licensed child care centers and homes with two or more stars shall receive the
9 market rate for that rated license level for that age group unless prohibited by
10 subsection (g) of this section.
11 (3) No payments shall be made for transportation services charged by child care
12 facilities.
13 (4) Payments for subsidized child care services for postsecondary education shall
14 be limited to a maximum of 20 months of enrollment. This shall not be
15 determined before a family's annual recertification period.
16 (5) The Department of Health and Human Services shall implement necessary
17 rule changes to restructure services, including, but not limited to, targeting
18 benefits to employment.
19 …
20 "SECTION 9D.3.(e) A market rate shall be calculated for child care centers and homes at
21 each rated license level for each county and for each age group or age category of enrollees and
22 shall be representative of fees charged to parents for each age group of enrollees within the
23 county. The Division of Child Development and Early Education shall also calculate a statewide
24 rate and regional market rate for each rated license level for each age category.
25 "SECTION 9D.3.(f) The Division of Child Development and Early Education shall continue
26 implementing policies that improve the quality of child care for subsidized children, including a
27 policy in which child care subsidies are paid, to the extent possible, for child care in the higher
28 quality centers and homes only. The Division shall define higher quality, and subsidy funds shall
29 not be paid for one- or two-star-rated facilities. For those counties with an inadequate number of
30 four- and five-star-rated facilities, the Division shall continue a transition period that allows the
31 facilities to continue to receive subsidy funds while the facilities work on the increased star
32 ratings. The Division may allow exemptions in counties where there is an inadequate number of
33 four- and five-star-rated facilities for non-star-rated programs, such as religious programs.
34 "SECTION 9D.3.(g) Facilities licensed pursuant to Article 7 of Chapter 110 of the General
35 Statutes and facilities operated pursuant to G.S. 110-106 may participate in the program that
36 provides for the purchase of care in child care facilities for minor children of needy families.
37 Except as authorized by subsection (f) of this section, no No separate licensing requirements shall
38 be used to select facilities to participate. In addition, child care facilities shall be required to meet
39 any additional applicable requirements of federal law or regulations. Child care arrangements
40 exempt from State regulation pursuant to Article 7 of Chapter 110 of the General Statutes shall
41 meet the requirements established by other State law and by the Social Services Commission.
42 County departments of social services or other local contracting agencies shall not use a
43 provider's failure to comply with requirements in addition to those specified in this subsection as
44 a condition for reducing the provider's subsidized child care rate.
45 …."
46 SECTION 1.(e) G.S. 110-90(4) is amended by adding a new sub-subdivision to read:
47 "f. A rated license shall have no impact on the rate at which a child care
48 facility is reimbursed for subsidized child care."
49 SECTION 1.(f) Nothing in this section shall be construed as impacting the
50 star-rating requirements for the NC Prekindergarten (NC Pre-K) program.
