3 by this subdivision.
4 Each child care facility shall provide indoor area equipment and
5 furnishings that are child size, sturdy, safe, and in good repair. Each child care
6 facility that provides outdoor area equipment and furnishings shall provide
7 outdoor area equipment and furnishings that are child size, sturdy, free of
8 hazards that pose a threat of serious injury to children while engaged in normal
9 play activities, and in good repair. The Commission shall adopt standards to
10 establish minimum requirements for equipment appropriate for the size of
11 child care facility. Space shall be available for proper storage of beds, cribs,
12 mats, cots, sleeping garments, and linens as well as designated space for each
13 child's personal belongings.
14 The Division of Child Development of the Department of Health and
15 Human Services shall establish and implement a policy that defines any
16 building which is currently approved for school occupancy and which houses
17 a public or private elementary or middle school to include the playgrounds
18 and athletic fields as part of the school building when that building is used to
19 serve school-age children in after-school out-of-school child care programs.
20 Playgrounds Except as provided in subdivision (6a) of this section,
21 playgrounds and athletic fields referenced in this section that do not meet
22 licensure standards promulgated by the North Carolina Child Care
23 Commission shall be noted on the program's licensure and rating
24 information."
25 SECTION 5.(a) G.S. 110-91 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
26 "(6a) Certain Exemptions for School-Age Children in Out-of-School Child Care. –
27 Notwithstanding any provision of law or rule to the contrary, any building and
28 grounds which are currently approved for school occupancy and which house
29 a public or private elementary or middle school shall be deemed to have met
30 the sanitation, fire, and building code requirements for a licensed child care
31 facility when the building and grounds are serving the same, or a subset of the
32 same, school-age children in an out-of-school child care program."
33 SECTION 5.(b) The Child Care Commission shall adopt or amend any rules to
34 ensure uniformity and consistency in application of the exemptions for school-age children in
35 out-of-school child care programs as provided in this section.
